    "comment": "Rationale: In inhibitory olfactory bulb synapses, the neurexin-3a/b deletion caused a selective decrease in presynaptic GABA release (Fig. 7) without a change in postsynaptic receptor composition (Fig. 6).\n\n1/11/2017 Pim\n- The paper uses DKO of neurexin-3alpha and neurexin-3beta genes (Fig.6/7) Data on the neurexin-3alpha is also included in Supplementary Fig. 2. Overall, the data for this paper directly supports a role for neurexin-3alpha, and a IGI relation of neurexin-3beta that is based on supposed functional redundancy between paralogs and author intent.\n- Authors note: '\"The constitutive ablation of Nrxn3α phenocopied the GABA release phenotype observed in Nrxn3α/β cKO cultured olfactory bulb neurons, suggesting that only Nrxn3α is essential for GABA release in granule cell neurons\". Experimental description: Conditional KO mice were studied",
